Ebi Shioyaki (Salt-Grilled Shrimp)

Ingredients (Serves 2)

Shrimp
	•	300 g (10.5 oz) large raw shrimp, shell-on, deveined

Seasoning
	•	3 g (1/2 tsp) fine sea salt

Fat & Aroma
	•	10 ml (2 tsp) neutral oil (rice bran or grapeseed)
	•	10 g (2 tsp) unsalted butter

Finishing
	•	15 ml (1 tbsp) fresh lemon juice

Shellfish-free option: use king oyster mushroom stems, scored and lightly salted, in equal weight.

⸻

Method
	1.	Prep & Season
Pat shrimp completely dry. Season evenly with sea salt. Rest 5 minutes to allow surface moisture to draw out, then re-pat dry if needed.
	2.	Heat Fat
Heat a heavy skillet over medium-high. Add oil, then butter. Allow butter to brown lightly until nutty and amber, not burnt.
	3.	Sear (Shell Side)
Place shrimp shell-side down in a single layer. Do not move. Sear 2 minutes until shells lightly char and aroma turns sweet.
	4.	Finish Cooking
Flip shrimp and cook flesh-side 1–2 minutes until just opaque and springy, with slight translucence at the center.
	5.	Acid Finish
Remove from heat. Add lemon juice and gently toss to coat. Serve immediately.

⸻

Optional Refinements
	•	Brown butter slightly darker for added bitterness and depth
	•	Finish with sudachi juice instead of lemon for a sharper citrus note
	•	Serve with grated daikon to cleanse the palate and balance richness